Class GoogleCloudStorageMapOutputWriter<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.appengine.tools.mapreduce.OutputWriter<KeyValue<K,V>>

        • com.google.appengine.tools.mapreduce.impl.GoogleCloudStorageMapOutputWriter<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of intermediate keys
    V - type of intermediate values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GoogleCloudStorageMapOutputWriter<K,V>
extends ShardingOutputWriter<K,V,com.google.appengine.tools.mapreduce.impl.GoogleCloudStorageMapOutputWriter.MapOutputWriter<K,V>>
    An OutputWriter that is used by the map stage and writes bytes to GCS, later to be used by the sort/merge stages. Content is written in a LevelDb log Format and then using the KeyValueMarshaller to marshall the individual record.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
